article.headline: Middle Tennessee 57, S. Dakota St. 56
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Desmond Yates scored 14 points and Theryn Hudson scored all 11 of his points in the second half as Middle Tennessee State defeated South Dakota State 57-56 on Monday. The Blue Raiders (11-11) erased an eight-point deficit in the last 11 minutes to keep the Jackrabbits (5-16) from winning their second straight game for just the second time this season. They last won back-to-back games Dec. 19 and Dec. 22. Kevin Kanaskie broke a 52-52 tie with a 3-pointer that gave Middle Tennessee the lead for good with 4:03 to play. The Blue Raiders trailed 49-41 with with 11 minutes left but scored nine straight points to go ahead 50-49 on Yates' dunk with 8:06 left. The Jackrabbits went back on top 52-50 on Jose Frias' layup and a free throw. SDSU was 20-for-28 from the free throw line, while Middle Tennessee made eight of nine attempts. Yates, who made five of six shots from the field, tied it at 52-52. Frias scored 15 points to lead SDSU. Matt Cadwell and Michael Loney added 10 points apiece. The Blue Raiders shot 52 percent from the field and outrebounds the Jackrabbits 30-22. SDSU shot 41 percent.
